6 7–504.
7 (a) (1) The Department shall adopt regulations that set eligibility guidelines
8 for State funding of Youth Suicide Prevention School Programs under this subtitle.
9 (2) The regulations shall:
10 (i) Establish procedures for developing local programs, in
11 cooperation with local education agencies, youth service bureaus, and community mental
12 health centers; and
13 (ii) Establish standards and policies for programs to offer:
14 1. Individual, family, and group counseling related to youth
15 suicide prevention;
16 2. Referral, crisis intervention, and information for students,
17 parents, and school personnel; and
18 3. Training for school personnel, and others responsible for
19 counseling or supervising student activities.
20 (b) A Youth Suicide Prevention School Program established under this subtitle
21 shall plan, fund, and implement educational programs, which may include any of the
22 following:
23 (1) Classroom instruction designed to achieve any of the following
24 objectives:
25 (i) Encourage sound decision making and promote ethical
26 development;
27 (ii) Increase pupils’ awareness of the relationship between drug and
28 alcohol use, GAMBLING, and youth suicide;
29 (iii) Teach pupils to recognize signs of suicidal tendencies, and other
30 facts about youth suicide;
31 (iv) Inform pupils of available community youth suicide prevention
32 services;

